newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Jakarta call money traded at 12.0/13.0 percent.
newsitem.headline: Jakarta call money traded at 12.0/13.0 percent.

text.p: Jakarta call money was traded at 12.0/13.0 percent on Friday morning on relatively brisk rupiah supply, dealers said.
They said liquidity was ample despite a neutral money policy from the central bank on Friday morning.
One Japanese bank dealer said overnight dollar supply was a bit tight in the morning, pushing the rate up to six percent from the usual rate of 5.5 percent.
He said a higher demand for overnight dollars might have caused operators to unload rupiah for dollars.
Dealers said longer-term rates for the rupiah remained stable although short-dated swap rates were easing in anticipation of sustained market liquidity.
The average overnight interbank rate on Thursday was 11.35 percent, compared with 11.47 percent on Wednesday.
